{"parse":{"title":"appearance","pageid":42510,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|appearaunce||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|en|frm|apparence}}, from {{der|en|la|apparentia|}}, from {{m|la|appareo|}}. Morphologically {{suffix|en|appear|ance}}. {{doublet|en|apparence|apparency}}. Displaced native {{ncog|ang|hīew||the way something looks or seems}} and {{m|ang|ætīewednes||act of appearing or coming into view}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/əˈpɪə.ɹəns/|a=RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/əˈpiɹ.əns/|a=GenAm}}, {{enPR|ə-pîrʹəns}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-appearance.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{hyph|en|ap|pear|ance}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# The act of [[appear]]ing or coming into sight; the act of becoming visible to the eye.\n#: {{ux|en|His sudden '''appearance''' surprised me.}}\n# A thing seen; a [[phenomenon]]; an [[apparition]].\n#: {{ux|en|There was a strange '''appearance''' in the sky.}}\n# The way something looks; personal [[presence]]\n#: {{syn|en|aspect|mien|make|face}}\n#* {{RQ:Milton Paradise Regained|book=Samson Agonistes|page=66|lines=99–101|passage=And now am come to ſee of whom ſuch noiſe <br> Hath walk'd about, and each limb to ſurvey, <br> If thy '''appearance''' anſwer loud report.}}\n#* {{RQ:Travers Cuckoo in the Nest|chapter=5|passage=The most rapid and most seductive transition in all human nature is that which attends the palliation of a ravenous appetite.{{...}}Can those harmless but refined fellow-diners be the selfish cads whose gluttony and personal '''appearance''' so raised your contemptuous wrath on your arrival?}}\n# Apparent [[likeness]]; the way which something or someone [[appear]]s to others.\n#: {{ux|en|Some people say I'm shallow because I care so much about my '''appearance'''.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=4 February 2016|author=Mark Hudson|title=KAWS, Yorkshire Sculpture Park, review: 'hypnotically compelling'|work=The Telegraph|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/art/what-to-see/kaws-yorkshire-sculpture-park-review/|page=|passage=KAWS’s first sculptures were limited edition toys for the Japanese brand Bounty Hunter, and the stylised figures distributed around YSP in a variety of postures – shielding their eyes from the sun, seated in apparent contemplation or leading a child-sized version of themselves over the sward – have the '''appearance''' of gigantic toys, with their instant legibility and machine-honed surfaces.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1769|title=The King James Bible|section={{w|Book of Numbers|Numbers}} ix. 15\n|passage=And on the day that the tabernacle was reared up the cloud covered the tabernacle, namely, the tent of the testimony: and at even there was upon the tabernacle as it were the '''appearance''' of fire, until the morning.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1769|title=The King James Bible|section={{w|Gospel of John|John}} vii. 24\n|passage=Judge not according to the '''appearance'''.}}\n#* '''2003''', {{w|Roy_Porter|Roy Porter}}, ''Flesh in the Age of Reason'', Ch.9, at p.150, 151:\n#*: 'Never be taken in by false '''appearances'''ʻ was {{w|Jonathan_Swift|Swift's}} habitual satirical message. 'In most Corporeal Beings, which have fallen under my Cognizance, the Outside hath been infinitely preferable to the In,' he elsewhere proclaimed. [...] The sordid reality beneath the mask haunted him: was all civilisation just dirt and derangement at heart? {{...}} Evidently man was not the ''homo rationalis'' he pretended to be but rather, at best, ''homo rationis capax'' ─ a creature capable of rationality, though by implication falling short.\n# {{lb|en|philosophy|theology}} That which is not [[substance]], [[essence]], [[hypostasis]]; the [[outward]] reality as opposed to the [[underlying]] reality\n#: {{ux|en|Catholicism teaches that the Eucharist, while remaining under the physical '''appearance''' of bread and wine, becomes really and truly the body and the blood of Christ.}}\n# The act of [[appear]]ing in a particular place, or in society, a company, or any proceedings; a coming before the public in a particular character.\n#: {{ux|en|A person makes his '''appearance''' as an historian, an artist, or an orator.}}\n#: {{ux|en|David Beckham's first '''appearance''' with the LA Galaxy at Giants Stadium against the New York Red Bulls last night drew a crowd of 66237.}}\n#* {{RQ:Milton Paradise Regained|text=Will he now retire, After '''appearance''', and again prolong Our expectation?}}\n# {{lb|en|legal}} An instance of someone coming into a [[court of law]] to be part of a [[trial]], [[lawsuit]] or other [[proceeding]], either [[in person]] or represented by an [[attorney]] or such like; a [[court appearance]]\n# {{lb|en|medical}} Chiefly used by [[nurse]]s: the act of [[defecation]] by a patient.\n#: {{ux|en|The patient had a small bowel obstruction and there was no '''appearance''' until after the obstruction resolved.}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|act of coming into sight}} {{l|en|arrival}}, {{l|en|manifestation}},\n* {{sense|a thing seen}} {{l|en|spectacle}}, {{l|en|apparition}}, {{l|en|phenomenon}}, {{l|en|presence}}\n* {{sense|aspect of a person}} {{l|en|aspect}}, {{l|en|air}}, {{l|en|figure}}, {{l|en|look}}, {{l|en|manner}}, {{l|en|mien}}\n* {{sense|outward show}} {{l|en|semblance}}, {{l|en|show}}, {{l|en|pretense}}, {{l|en|façade}} or [[facade]]\n* {{sense|act of appearing in public}} {{l|en|debut}}\n\n====Antonyms====\n* {{l|en|non-appearance}}, {{l|en|nonappearance}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|appearanced|coappearance|misappearance|abrupt appearance|court appearance|disappearance|keep up appearances|plate appearance|put in an appearance|reappearance|save appearances|appearance money|make an appearance|to all appearance}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|en|appear|apparent}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|the act of appearing or coming into sight}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t|af|verskyning}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|pamje|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|ظُهُور|m}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|з'яўле́нне|n}}, {{t|be|паяўле́нне|n}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|появя́ване}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|aparició}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|出現|tr=chūxiàn}}\n* Czech: {{t|cs|objevení se|n}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|verschijning|f}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|apero|}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|ilmestyminen}}, {{t+|fi|ilmaantuminen}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|apparition|f}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|aparición|f}}\n* German: {{t|de|Erscheinen|n}}, {{t+|de|Auftritt|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|εμφάνιση|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|φάσις|f}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t-needed|haw}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|הופעה|f|tr=hofa'a}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|दिखना}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|megjelenés}}, {{t+|hu|feltűnés}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|nochtadh|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|apparizione|f}}, {{t+|it|comparsa|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|出現|tr=しゅつげん, shutsugen}}\n* Javanese: {{t+|jv|rupa}}, {{t+|jv|warna}}, {{t|jv|warni}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t|ckb|دەرپەڕین}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|појавување|n}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|kōwhitinga}} {{qualifier|of stars, planets etc in the night sky}}, {{t|mi|putanga}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|ætīewednes}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|پدیدار شدن|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|aparição|f}}, {{t+|pt|aparecimento|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|apariție|f}}, {{t+|ro|înfățișare|f}}, {{t+|ro|aparență|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|появле́ние|n}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|taisbeanadh|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t+|sh|pojavljivanje}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|apparizziuni|f}}, {{t|scn|cumparizziuni|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|pojavitev|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|aparición|f}}, {{t+|es|aparecimiento|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|ankomst}}\n* Tahitian: {{t-needed|ty}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|zuhur}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|поя́ва}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|xuất hiện}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|a thing seen}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|مَظْهَر|m}}\n* Belarusian: {{t+|be|з'я́ва|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|явле́ние}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|aparició}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|aperaĵo}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|ilmiö}}, {{t+|fi|ilmentymä}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|apparition|f}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|aparición|f}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|उपस्थित}}\n* Indonesian: {{t|id|kenampakan}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|apparizione|f}}, {{t+|it|visione|f}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|hīew|n}}, {{t|ang|hīewung|f}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|zjawisko|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|aparição|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|apariție|f}}, {{t+|ro|viziune|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|явле́ние|n}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|apparizziuni|f}}, {{t|scn|visiuni|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|aparición|f}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|framträdande}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|з'я́висько}}, {{t|uk|ви́димість}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|hiện tượng}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|personal presence, form or look}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|مَظْهَر|m}}, {{t|ar|شَكْل|m}}, {{t|ar|هَيْئَة|f}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|արտաքին}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|চেহেৰা}}, {{t|as|ৰূপ}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|zahir}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|аблі́чча|n}}, {{t|be|во́нкавы вы́гляд|m}}, {{t+|be|вы́гляд|m}}, {{t|be|во́нкавасць|f}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|চেহারা}}, {{t+|bn|রূপ}}, {{t+|bn|সুরত}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|въ́ншност}}, {{t|bg|въ́ншен вид}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|aparença}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|外貌|tr=ngoi6 maau6}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|外貌|tr=wàimào}}, {{t+|cmn|模樣|tr=múyàng}}, {{t+|cmn|樣子|tr=yàngzi}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|aspekto}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|julkiasu}}, {{t+|fi|ulkomuoto}}, {{t+|fi|ulkonäkö}}, {{t|fi|tuntomerkit}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|apparence}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|შესახედაობა}}, {{t|ka|გარეგნობა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Aussehen|n}}\n* Gothic: {{t|got|𐍃𐌹𐌿𐌽𐍃|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|εμφάνιση|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ἰδέα|f}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t-needed|haw}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|रूप}}, {{t|hi|रूप-रंग|m}}, {{t+|hi|भेस|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|kinézet}}, {{t+|hu|megjelenés}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|kaanu}}, {{t|izh|koosi}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|comharthaí|m-p}}, {{t|ga|comharthaí aithne|m-p}}, {{t|ga|comharthaí sóirt|m-p}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|apparenza|f}}, {{t+|it|aspetto|m}}, {{t+|it|sembianza|f}}, {{t+|it|aria|f}}, {{t+|it|cera|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|様子|tr=ようす, yōsu}}, {{t+|ja|外観|tr=がいかん, gaikan}}, {{t+|ja|見掛け|tr=みかけ, mikake}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|сиық}}\n* Korean: {{t-needed|ko}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|speciēs|f}}, {{t|la|vultum|n}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|изглед|m}}\n* Middle English: {{t|enm|wlite}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|iʼnoolinígíí}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|hīew|n}}, {{t|ang|ansīen|f}}, {{t|ang|wlite|m}}, {{t|ang|andwlita|m}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|wygląd|m}}, {{qualifier|literary}} {{t+|pl|aparycja|f}}, {{t+|pl|powierzchowność|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|aparência|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|înfățișare|f}}, {{t+|ro|aspect|n}} (exterior), {{t+|ro|aparență|f}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|apparientscha|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|вне́шность|f}}, {{t+|ru|вне́шний вид|m}}, {{t+|ru|о́блик|m}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+|sa|रूप|n}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t+|sh|pojava}}, {{t|sh|izgled}}, {{t+|sh|vanjština}}\n* Sicilian: {{t+|scn|figura|f}}, {{t+|scn|aspettu|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|videz|m}}, {{t|sl|zunanjost|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|apariencia|f}}, {{t+|es|hechura|f}}, {{t+|es|estampa|f}}, {{t+|es|talle|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|utseende|n}}\n* Tahitian: {{t|ty|hohoʻa}}\n* Turkish:\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|نمایش|tr=nümayiş}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|зо́внішній ви́гляд}}, {{t|uk|зо́внішність}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|bề ngoài}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|semblance, or apparent likeness}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|شَكْل|m}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|во́нкавасць|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|при́лика}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|aspecte|m}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|vzhled|m}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|aanblik}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|ulkonäkö}}, {{t+|fi|ulkomuoto}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|apparence|f}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Aussehen|n}}\n* Greek:\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ὄψις|f}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|penampilan}}, {{t+|id|tampang}}\n* Irish: {{t+|ga|dealramh|m}}, {{t|ga|cruth|m}}, {{t|ga|cuma|f}}, {{t|ga|aithnid|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|apparenza|f}}, {{t+|it|aspetto|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|見た目|tr=[[みため]], mitame}}, {{t+|ja|外見|tr=がいけん, gaiken}}; {{qualifier|formally}} {{t+|ja|外観|tr=がいかん, gaikan}}, {{t+|ja|体裁|tr=ていさい, teisai}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|외모(外貌)}}, {{t|ko|외양(外樣)}}, {{t+|ko|외관(外觀)}}, {{t+|ko|겉모습}}, {{t+|ko|볼품}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|aspectus|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|aparência|f}}, {{t+|pt|aspecto|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|aparență|f}}, {{t+|ro|înfățișare|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|вне́шность|f}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|coltas|m}}\n* Sicilian: {{t+|scn|apparenzia|f}}, {{t+|scn|ariu|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|videz|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|apariencia|f}}, {{t+|es|aire|m}}, {{t+|es|aspecto|m}}, {{t+|es|viso|m}}, {{t+|es|cariz|m}}, {{t+|es|pergeño|m}}, {{t+|es|pergenio|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|tillstymmelse}}, {{t+|sv|sken}}, {{t+|sv|utseende}}\n* Thai: {{t|th|รูปลักษณ์}}, {{t|th|สารรูป}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|зо́внішність}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|the act of appearing in a particular place, or in society, a company, or any proceedings}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|esiintyminen}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|εμφάνιση|f}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|उपस्थिति|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|presentazione|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|世間体|tr=sekentei}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|ætīewednes|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|aparecimento|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|prezentare|f}}, {{t+|ro|înfățișare|f}}, {{t+|ro|apariție|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|появле́ние|n}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|prisintazziuni|f}}, {{t|scn|participazziuni|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|aparición|f}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|uppträdande}}, {{t+|sv|framträdande}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|поя́ва}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|the coming into court of either of the parties}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|явя́ване}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|compareixença|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|出庭}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|comparitie|f}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|saapuminen}}, {{t+|fi|ilmestyminen}}, {{t+|fi|näyttäytyminen}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|comparution|f}}\n*: Middle French: {{t|frm|comparution|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|εμφάνιση|f}}, {{t+|el|προσέλευση|f}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|पेशी|f}}\n* Indonesian: {{t|id|komparisi}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|láithreas|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|comparizione|f}}, {{t+|it|comparsa|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|出廷|tr=しゅってい, shuttei}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|stawiennictwo|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|comparecimento|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|înfățișare|f}} (la judecătorie)\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|я́вка|f}}\n* Sicilian: {{t|scn|cumparizziuni|f}}, {{t+|scn|cumparsa|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|aparición|f}}, {{t+|es|comparecencia|f}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|я́вка}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:Webster 1913|appearance}}\n\n{{C|en|Appearance}}"}}